data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**Sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** In .NET 10 you had the sync-over-async opt-in; in EF Core 11 that opt-in is gone. All synchronous calls — `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()` — **always throw at runtime**. There is no workaround flag.

**Fix:** Convert every method to its async equivalent:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple up the call stack — all callers must also become `async`/`await`. Remove any `.EnableSyncOverAsync()` or similar opt-in configuration from your `DbContext` setup, as it no longer has any effect.
